1. set up Amazon EC2 virtual machine
	- Free tier, 15G Internet bandwidth
	- Ubuntu Server 14.04 LTS (HVM), SSD Volume Type
	- Inbound poliy: open UDP port 500 ans UDP port 4500
	
2. Install racoon: sudo apt-get install racoon
3. Prepare your VPN preference: internal IP segment, ID(IOS called "group name"), PSK(pre-shared key), user/passwd;
4. In Ubuntu linux, adduser as "user/passwd";
5. Configurate racoon: racoon.conf (internal IP segment), psk.txt(ID,PSK);
6. start racoon: sudo racoon;
7. configrate source-NAT: iptables
8. Check Cisco IPsec client, if not, install it. (IOS and OSX have built-in Cisco Ipsec client)


DONE

